Super Plug Shader (by VRCFury) is a free mesh deformation system that can be used to deform meshes towards a target, and is a full backwards-compatible replacement for DPS (Dynamic Penetration System by Raliv) and TPS (Thry Penetration System in Poiyomi Pro). In addition to being free, it supports a wide variety of shaders without them needing to hard-code support, including Backlace! Please click the link below to open the documentation for it in order to set it up!

LTCGI (by _pi_) is a plug-and-play realtime area lighting solution for VRChat. To enable this, please make sure you also include the LTCGI package in your project as it requires its own shader functions to work. When enabled, your material will then automatically use LTCGIs lighting.
Standard Specular has no stylised options - try changing the specular mode to see settings here!
This affect needs to read Depth from the scene! Ensure that your world either has a real-time light enabled or that the Depth Writer prefab is in the scene (provided with Backlace).
